## Update a Specific Order


```shell
curl "<%= config[:endpoint] %>order/<%= config[:example_order] %>" \\
  -X PATCH \\
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.api+json" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <%= config[:example_token] %>" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/vnd.api+json" \\
  -d '{
        "data": {
          "type": "order", 
          "id": "<%= config[:example_order] %>", 
          "attributes": {
            "deliveryDate": "2020-01-02"
          }
        }
      }'
```

> If successful, the above command returns the modified resource in the same structure

This endpoint updates and upon success retrieves a specified order.

<aside class="notice">
When sending json data, basically when not using the GET method, make sure to include `Content-Type: application/vnd.api+json`.
</aside>

